</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[144,1104,1271,1430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faubel" authorityYear="1983" box="[144,296,1309,1333]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pleioplanidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Pleioplanidae</taxonomicName>
with oval body shape. Tentacular and cerebral eye-spots present; tentacles small. Male copulatory apparatus with spermiducal bulbs and true seminal vesicle; prostatic vesicle of 
<emphasis box="[465,556,1374,1397]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">atomata</emphasis>
- 
<typeStatus box="[564,616,1374,1398]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1480">type</typeStatus>
; muscularised elongated ejaculatory duct, provided with a stylet. Without vagina bulbosa or Lang’ s vesicle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
